%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
# Introduction to Wolfram Language
Let's explore the fundamental concepts with practical examples.

<br />

## Pattern Matching and Transformation Rules
Pattern matching is at the heart of Wolfram Language. Let's start with a simple example:

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Type: Input
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
{1,1,2,2,2,2} /. {2 -> 1, 1 -> 0}

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Type: Output
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
{0,0,1,1,1,1}

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Props:
  Hidden: true
Type: Input
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
.md
Integer numbers are atoms of the language on which we can apply transformation rules. We can also use more general patterns:

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Display: markdown
Type: Output
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Integer numbers are atoms of the language on which we can apply transformation rules. We can also use more general patterns:

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Type: Input
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
{0,0,1,1,1,1} /. {any_Integer :> any / 2}

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Type: Output
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
{0,0,(*FB[*)((1)(*,*)/(*,*)(2))(*]FB*),(*FB[*)((1)(*,*)/(*,*)(2))(*]FB*),(*FB[*)((1)(*,*)/(*,*)(2))(*]FB*),(*FB[*)((1)(*,*)/(*,*)(2))(*]FB*)}

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Props:
  Hidden: true
Type: Input
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
.md
Any output expression is editable and can be reevaluated.

## Advanced Pattern Matching
Pattern matching can use conditions and more complex structures:

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Display: markdown
Type: Output
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Any output expression is editable and can be reevaluated.

## Advanced Pattern Matching
Pattern matching can use conditions and more complex structures:

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Type: Input
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
{0,0,(*FB[*)((1)(*,*)/(*,*)(2))(*]FB*),(*FB[*)((1)(*,*)/(*,*)(2))(*]FB*),(*FB[*)((1)(*,*)/(*,*)(2))(*]FB*),(*FB[*)((1)(*,*)/(*,*)(2))(*]FB*)} /. {
  any_?NumericQ :> {RGBColor[any, 1-any, 1], any}
}

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Type: Output
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
{{(*VB[*)(RGBColor[0, 1, 1])(*,*)(*"1:eJxTTMoPSmNiYGAo5gUSYZmp5S6pyflFiSX5RcEsQBHn4PCQNGaQPAeQCHJ3cs7PyS8qYoACKOODPZwBANmdEHU="*)(*]VB*),0},{(*VB[*)(RGBColor[0, 1, 1])(*,*)(*"1:eJxTTMoPSmNiYGAo5gUSYZmp5S6pyflFiSX5RcEsQBHn4PCQNGaQPAeQCHJ3cs7PyS8qYoACKOODPZwBANmdEHU="*)(*]VB*),0},{(*VB[*)(RGBColor[1/2, 1/2, 1])(*,*)(*"1:eJxTTMoPSmNiYGAo5gUSYZmp5S6pyflFiSX5RcEsQBHn4PCQNGaQPAeQCHJ3cs7PyS8qYgCDB/bojA/2AO8aEYQ="*)(*]VB*),(*FB[*)((1)(*,*)/(*,*)(2))(*]FB*)},{(*VB[*)(RGBColor[1/2, 1/2, 1])(*,*)(*"1:eJxTTMoPSmNiYGAo5gUSYZmp5S6pyflFiSX5RcEsQBHn4PCQNGaQPAeQCHJ3cs7PyS8qYgCDB/bojA/2AO8aEYQ="*)(*]VB*),(*FB[*)((1)(*,*)/(*,*)(2))(*]FB*)},{(*VB[*)(RGBColor[1/2, 1/2, 1])(*,*)(*"1:eJxTTMoPSmNiYGAo5gUSYZmp5S6pyflFiSX5RcEsQBHn4PCQNGaQPAeQCHJ3cs7PyS8qYgCDB/bojA/2AO8aEYQ="*)(*]VB*),(*FB[*)((1)(*,*)/(*,*)(2))(*]FB*)},{(*VB[*)(RGBColor[1/2, 1/2, 1])(*,*)(*"1:eJxTTMoPSmNiYGAo5gUSYZmp5S6pyflFiSX5RcEsQBHn4PCQNGaQPAeQCHJ3cs7PyS8qYgCDB/bojA/2AO8aEYQ="*)(*]VB*),(*FB[*)((1)(*,*)/(*,*)(2))(*]FB*)}}

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Props:
  Hidden: true
Type: Input
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
.md
As you can see, Wolfram Language does not distinguish between data types. Colors, numbers, functions--they are all just symbolic expressions.

You can also format output for readability:

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Display: markdown
Type: Output
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
As you can see, Wolfram Language does not distinguish between data types. Colors, numbers, functions--they are all just symbolic expressions.

You can also format output for readability:

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Type: Input
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
% // Transpose // TableForm

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Type: Output
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
(*GB[*){{(*VB[*)(RGBColor[0, 1, 1])(*,*)(*"1:eJxTTMoPSmNiYGAo5gUSYZmp5S6pyflFiSX5RcEsQBHn4PCQNGaQPAeQCHJ3cs7PyS8qYoACKOODPZwBANmdEHU="*)(*]VB*)(*|*),(*|*)(*VB[*)(RGBColor[0, 1, 1])(*,*)(*"1:eJxTTMoPSmNiYGAo5gUSYZmp5S6pyflFiSX5RcEsQBHn4PCQNGaQPAeQCHJ3cs7PyS8qYoACKOODPZwBANmdEHU="*)(*]VB*)(*|*),(*|*)(*VB[*)(RGBColor[1/2, 1/2, 1])(*,*)(*"1:eJxTTMoPSmNiYGAo5gUSYZmp5S6pyflFiSX5RcEsQBHn4PCQNGaQPAeQCHJ3cs7PyS8qYgCDB/bojA/2AO8aEYQ="*)(*]VB*)(*|*),(*|*)(*VB[*)(RGBColor[1/2, 1/2, 1])(*,*)(*"1:eJxTTMoPSmNiYGAo5gUSYZmp5S6pyflFiSX5RcEsQBHn4PCQNGaQPAeQCHJ3cs7PyS8qYgCDB/bojA/2AO8aEYQ="*)(*]VB*)(*|*),(*|*)(*VB[*)(RGBColor[1/2, 1/2, 1])(*,*)(*"1:eJxTTMoPSmNiYGAo5gUSYZmp5S6pyflFiSX5RcEsQBHn4PCQNGaQPAeQCHJ3cs7PyS8qYgCDB/bojA/2AO8aEYQ="*)(*]VB*)(*|*),(*|*)(*VB[*)(RGBColor[1/2, 1/2, 1])(*,*)(*"1:eJxTTMoPSmNiYGAo5gUSYZmp5S6pyflFiSX5RcEsQBHn4PCQNGaQPAeQCHJ3cs7PyS8qYgCDB/bojA/2AO8aEYQ="*)(*]VB*)}(*||*),(*||*){0(*|*),(*|*)0(*|*),(*|*)(*FB[*)((1)(*,*)/(*,*)(2))(*]FB*)(*|*),(*|*)(*FB[*)((1)(*,*)/(*,*)(2))(*]FB*)(*|*),(*|*)(*FB[*)((1)(*,*)/(*,*)(2))(*]FB*)(*|*),(*|*)(*FB[*)((1)(*,*)/(*,*)(2))(*]FB*)}}(*]GB*)

